A Kaduna Chief Magistrates’ Court on Wednesday ordered that a driver, Salahudeen Isah, 50, who allegedly defiled his friend’s nine-year-old daughter, be remanded in prison, pending legal advice. Magistrate Hajara Dauda, who did not take the plea of Isah, ordered the police to duplicate the case file and send it to the Kaduna State Directorate of Public Prosecution for legal advice. ALSO READ: Organisation provides humanitarian support to 251, 513 IDPs in northeast Dauda adjourned the matter until Sept. 30 for mention. Court convicts two students of Ekiti State University for… Court remands truck pusher for defiling 6-year-old girl Court remands man for allegedly defiling 10-year-old boy Court remands 2 traders over alleged robbery Isah, who resides in Kakuri in Kaduna State, is charged with defilement. Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Sunday Baba told the court that on Aug. 30, Isah allegedly lured his friend’s nine-year-old daughter into his room and defiled her. Baba said that the matter was reported to the State Criminal Investigation Department, by the girl’s father. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of Section 258 of the Kaduna State Penal Code Laws 2017. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
